  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/36912500/keycloak-tomcat-adapter-is-there-a-alternative-path-for-keycloak-json",
  "title" : "Keycloak-Tomcat-Adapter: Is there a alternative path for &#39;keycloak.json&#39;?",
  "body" : "<p>I try to secure my Java Servlet application with keycloak. All works fine but I don't like the fact that my 'keycloak.json' file is inside my release located. The reason is, if the keycloak definitions are inside my war, so I need for different installations different build processes or the same client credentials on different installations.</p>\n\n<p>My idea was now to place the 'keycloak.json' outside my WEB-INF. Is this possible? Other ideas to solve this problem are also welcome.</p>\n"
}